x25CountersTable.name: x25CountersTable
x25CountersTable.description: Runtime counters table, one row per port

x25CountEntry.name: x25CountEntry
x25CountEntry.description: The set of counters for one port.

x25CountPortRef.name: x25CountPortRef
x25CountPortRef.description: The Port reference on which the X25 is running.

x25CallReqTxs.name: x25CallReqTxs
x25CallReqTxs.description: The number of requests transmitted for a connection.

x25CallReqRxs.name: x25CallReqRxs
x25CallReqRxs.description: The number of requests received for a connection.

x25RegisterReqTxs.name: x25RegisterReqTxs
x25RegisterReqTxs.description: The number of register packets sent. Register packets are used to exchange registration information.

x25RegisterReqRxs.name: x25RegisterReqRxs
x25RegisterReqRxs.description: The number of register packets received.

x25DataSegmentsTxs.name: x25DataSegmentsTxs
x25DataSegmentsTxs.description: The number of 64 bytes data blocks sent.

x25DataSegmentsRxs.name: x25DataSegmentsRxs
x25DataSegmentsRxs.description: The number of 64 bytes data blocks received.

x25DiagnosticPktsTxs.name: x25DiagnosticPktsTxs
x25DiagnosticPktsTxs.description: The number of error information packets sent.

x25DiagnosticPktsRxs.name: x25DiagnosticPktsRxs
x25DiagnosticPktsRxs.description: The number of error information packets received.

x25UnknownPktsTxs.name: x25UnknownPktsTxs
x25UnknownPktsTxs.description: The number of packets that could not be recognized as following the X.25 structure sent.

x25UnknownPktsRxs.name: x25UnknownPktsRxs
x25UnknownPktsRxs.description: The number of packets that could not be recognized as following the X.25 structure received.

x25VCCallParmTable.name: x25VCCallParmTable
x25VCCallParmTable.description: This table contains only the objects of the Internet x25CallParmTable which are available from the EiconCard. For the complete description of x25CallParmTable, please refer to RFC1382.

x25VCCallParmPortIndex.name: x25VCCallParmPortIndex
x25VCCallParmPortIndex.description: The Port reference on which the X25 is running.

x25VCCallParmInPacketSize.name: x25VCCallParmInPacketSize
x25VCCallParmInPacketSize.description: The maximum receive packet size in octets for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE means use a default size of 128.

x25VCCallParmOutPacketSize.name: x25VCCallParmOutPacketSize
x25VCCallParmOutPacketSize.description: The maximum transmit packet size in octets for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE default means use a default size of 128.

x25VCCallParmInWindowSize.name: x25VCCallParmInWindowSize
x25VCCallParmInWindowSize.description: The receive window size for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE default means use 2.

x25VCCallParmOutWindowSize.name: x25VCCallParmOutWindowSize
x25VCCallParmOutWindowSize.description: The transmit window size for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE default means use 2.

x25VCCallParmUserData.name: x25VCCallParmUserData
x25VCCallParmUserData.description: The call user data as placed in the packet. A zero length string indicates no call user data. If both the circuit call parameters and the PLE default have call user data defined, the data from the circuit call parameters will be used. If only the PLE has data defined, the PLE entry will be used. If neither the circuit call parameters or the PLE default entry has a value, no call user data will be sent.

x25VCCallParmCallingNetworkFacilities.name: x25VCCallParmCallingNetworkFacilities
x25VCCallParmCallingNetworkFacilities.description: The calling network facilities. The facilities are encoded here exactly as encoded in the call packet. These facilities do not include the marker facility code. A zero length string in the entry for the parameter to use when establishing a circuit means use the PLE default. A zero length string in the entry for PLE default parameters indicates no default facilities.

x25VCCallParmCalledNetworkFacilities.name: x25VCCallParmCalledNetworkFacilities
x25VCCallParmCalledNetworkFacilities.description: The called network facilities. The facilities are encoded here exactly as encoded in the call packet. These facilities do not include the marker facility code. A zero length string in the entry for the parameter to use when establishing a circuit means use the PLE default. A zero length string in the entry for PLE default parameters indicates no default facilities.

x25OperTable.name: x25OperTable
x25OperTable.description: The operation parameters in use by the X.25 PLE.

x25OperIndex.name: x25OperIndex
x25OperIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the X.25 interface.

x25OperInterfaceMode.name: x25OperInterfaceMode
x25OperInterfaceMode.description: Identifies DCE/DTE mode in which the interface operates. A value of dxe indicates the role will be determined by XID negotiation at the Link Layer and that negotiation has not yet taken place.

x25OperMaxActiveCircuits.name: x25OperMaxActiveCircuits
x25OperMaxActiveCircuits.description: Maximum number of circuits this PLE can support.

x25OperPacketSequencing.name: x25OperPacketSequencing
x25OperPacketSequencing.description: The modulus of the packet sequence number space.

x25OperRestartTimer.name: x25OperRestartTimer
x25OperRestartTimer.description: The T20 restart timer in milliseconds.

x25OperCallTimer.name: x25OperCallTimer
x25OperCallTimer.description: The T21 Call timer in milliseconds.

x25OperResetTimer.name: x25OperResetTimer
x25OperResetTimer.description: The T22 Reset timer in milliseconds.

x25OperClearTimer.name: x25OperClearTimer
x25OperClearTimer.description: The T23 Clear timer in milliseconds.

x25OperWindowTimer.name: x25OperWindowTimer
x25OperWindowTimer.description: The T24 window status transmission timer milliseconds. A value of 2147483647 indicates no window timer in use.

x25OperDataRxmtTimer.name: x25OperDataRxmtTimer
x25OperDataRxmtTimer.description: The T25 Data Retransmission timer in milliseconds. A value of 2147483647 indicates no data retransmission timer in use.

x25OperInterruptTimer.name: x25OperInterruptTimer
x25OperInterruptTimer.description: The T26 Interrupt timer in milliseconds. A value of 2147483647 indicates interrupts are not being used.

x25OperRejectTimer.name: x25OperRejectTimer
x25OperRejectTimer.description: The T27 Reject retransmission timer in milliseconds. A value of 2147483647 indicates no reject timer in use.

x25OperRegistrationRequestTimer.name: x25OperRegistrationRequestTimer
x25OperRegistrationRequestTimer.description: The T28 registration timer in milliseconds. A value of 2147483647 indicates no registration timer in use.

x25OperMinimumRecallTimer.name: x25OperMinimumRecallTimer
x25OperMinimumRecallTimer.description: Minimum time interval between unsuccessful call attempts in milliseconds.

x25OperDataRxmtCount.name: x25OperDataRxmtCount
x25OperDataRxmtCount.description: The R25 Data retransmission count. This value is undefined if the x25OperDataRxmtTimer indicates no timer in use.

x25OperRejectCount.name: x25OperRejectCount
x25OperRejectCount.description: The R27 reject retransmission count. This value is undefined if the x25OperRejectTimer indicates no timer in use.

x25OperRegistrationRequestCount.name: x25OperRegistrationRequestCount
x25OperRegistrationRequestCount.description: The R28 Registration retransmission Count. This value is undefined if the x25OperREgistrationRequestTimer indicates no timer in use.

x25OperNumberPVCs.name: x25OperNumberPVCs
x25OperNumberPVCs.description: The number of PVC configured for this PLE. The PVCs use channel numbers from 1 to this number.

x25OperDefCallParamId.name: x25OperDefCallParamId
x25OperDefCallParamId.description: This identifies the instance of the x25CallParmIndex for the entry in the x25CallParmTable that contains the default call parameters for this PLE.

x25OperLocalAddress.name: x25OperLocalAddress
x25OperLocalAddress.description: The local address for this PLE subnetwork. A zero length address maybe returned by PLEs that only support PVCs.

x25OperDataLinkId.name: x25OperDataLinkId
x25OperDataLinkId.description: This identifies the instance of the index object in the first table of the most device specific MIB for the interface used by this PLE.

x25OperProtocolVersionSupported.name: x25OperProtocolVersionSupported
x25OperProtocolVersionSupported.description: Identifies the version of the X.25 protocol this interface supports. Object identifiers for common versions are defined below in the x25ProtocolVersion subtree.

x25StatTable.name: x25StatTable
x25StatTable.description: Statistics information about this X.25 PLE.

x25StatIndex.name: x25StatIndex
x25StatIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the X.25 interface.

x25StatInCalls.name: x25StatInCalls
x25StatInCalls.description: The number of incoming calls received.

x25StatInCallRefusals.name: x25StatInCallRefusals
x25StatInCallRefusals.description: The number of incoming calls refused. This includes calls refused by the PLE and by higher layers. This also includes calls cleared because of restricted fast select.

x25StatInProviderInitiatedClears.name: x25StatInProviderInitiatedClears
x25StatInProviderInitiatedClears.description: The number of clear requests with a cause code other than DTE initiated.

x25StatInRemotelyInitiatedResets.name: x25StatInRemotelyInitiatedResets
x25StatInRemotelyInitiatedResets.description: The number of reset requests received with cause code DTE initiated.

x25StatInProviderInitiatedResets.name: x25StatInProviderInitiatedResets
x25StatInProviderInitiatedResets.description: The number of reset requests received with cause code other than DTE initiated.

x25StatInRestarts.name: x25StatInRestarts
x25StatInRestarts.description: The number of remotely initiated (including provider initiated) restarts experienced by the PLE excluding the restart associated with bringing up the PLE interface. This only counts restarts received when the PLE already has an established connection with the remove PLE.

x25StatInDataPackets.name: x25StatInDataPackets
x25StatInDataPackets.description: The number of data packets received.

x25StatInAccusedOfProtocolErrors.name: x25StatInAccusedOfProtocolErrors
x25StatInAccusedOfProtocolErrors.description: The number of packets received containing a procedure error cause code. These include clear, reset, restart, or diagnostic packets.

x25StatInInterrupts.name: x25StatInInterrupts
x25StatInInterrupts.description: The number of interrupt packets received by the PLE or over the PVC/VC.

x25StatOutCallFailures.name: x25StatOutCallFailures
x25StatOutCallFailures.description: The number of call attempts which failed. This includes calls that were cleared because of restrictive fast select.

x25StatOutInterrupts.name: x25StatOutInterrupts
x25StatOutInterrupts.description: The number of interrupt packets send by the PLE or over the PVC/VC.

x25StatOutDataPackets.name: x25StatOutDataPackets
x25StatOutDataPackets.description: The number of data packets sent by this PLE.

x25StatOutgoingCircuits.name: x25StatOutgoingCircuits
x25StatOutgoingCircuits.description: The number of active outgoing circuits. This includes call requests sent but not yet confirmed. This does not count PVCs.

x25StatIncomingCircuits.name: x25StatIncomingCircuits
x25StatIncomingCircuits.description: The number of active Incoming Circuits. This includes call indications received but not yet acknowledged. This does not count PVCs.

x25StatTwowayCircuits.name: x25StatTwowayCircuits
x25StatTwowayCircuits.description: The number of active two-way Circuits. This includes call requests sent but not yet confirmed. This does not count PVCs.

x25StatRestartTimeouts.name: x25StatRestartTimeouts
x25StatRestartTimeouts.description: The number of times the T20 restart timer expired.

x25StatCallTimeouts.name: x25StatCallTimeouts
x25StatCallTimeouts.description: The number of times the T21 call timer expired.

x25StatResetTimeouts.name: x25StatResetTimeouts
x25StatResetTimeouts.description: The number of times the T22 reset timer expired.

x25StatClearTimeouts.name: x25StatClearTimeouts
x25StatClearTimeouts.description: The number of times the T23 clear timer expired.

x25StatDataRxmtTimeouts.name: x25StatDataRxmtTimeouts
x25StatDataRxmtTimeouts.description: The number of times the T25 data timer expired.

x25StatInterruptTimeouts.name: x25StatInterruptTimeouts
x25StatInterruptTimeouts.description: The number of times the T26 interrupt timer expired.

x25StatRetryCountExceededs.name: x25StatRetryCountExceededs
x25StatRetryCountExceededs.description: The number of times a retry counter was exhausted.

x25StatClearCountExceededs.name: x25StatClearCountExceededs
x25StatClearCountExceededs.description: The number of times the R23 clear count was exceeded.

x25ChannelTable.name: x25ChannelTable
x25ChannelTable.description: These objects contain information about the channel number configuration in an X.25 PLE. These values are the configured values. changes in these values after the interfaces has started may not be reflected in the operating PLE.

x25ChannelEntry.name: x25ChannelEntry
x25ChannelEntry.reference: This provides the information available in 10733 logicalChannelAssignments.

x25ChannelIndex.name: x25ChannelIndex
x25ChannelIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the X.25 Interface.

x25ChannelHIC.name: x25ChannelHIC
x25ChannelHIC.description: Highest Incoming channel. A value of zero indicates no channels in this range.

x25ChannelHTC.name: x25ChannelHTC
x25ChannelHTC.description: Highest Two-way channel. A value of zero indicates no channels in this range.

x25ChannelHOC.name: x25ChannelHOC
x25ChannelHOC.description: Highest outgoing channel. A value of zero indicates no channels in this range.

x25CircuitTable.name: x25CircuitTable
x25CircuitTable.description: These objects contain general information about a specific circuit of an X.25 PLE.

x25CircuitIndex.name: x25CircuitIndex
x25CircuitIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the X.25 Interface.

x25CircuitChannel.name: x25CircuitChannel
x25CircuitChannel.description: The channel number for this circuit.

x25CircuitStatus.name: x25CircuitStatus
x25CircuitStatus.reference: See ISO 8208, table 33 for (p<n>) state table
x25CircuitStatus.description: This object reports the current status of the circuit. An existing instance of this object can only be set to startClear, startPvcResetting, or invalid. An instance with the value calling or open can only be set to startClear and that action will start clearing the circuit. An instance with the value PVC can only be set to startPvcResetting or invalid and that action resets the PVC or deletes the circuit respectively. The values startClear or startPvcResetting will never be returned by an agent. An attempt to set the status of an existing instance to a value other than one of these values will result in an error. A non-existing instance can be set to PVC to create a PVC if the implementation supports dynamic creation of PVCs. Some implementations may only allow creation and deletion of PVCs if the interface is down. Since the instance identifier will supply the PLE index and the channel number, setting this object alone supplies sufficient information to create the instance. All the DEFVAL clauses for the other objects of this table are appropriate for creating a PVC; PLEs creating entries for placed or accepted calls will use values appropriate for the call rather than the value of the DEFVAL clause. Two managers trying to create the same PVC can determine from the return code which manager succeeded and which failed (the failing manager fails because it can not set a value of PVC for an existing object). An entry in the closed or invalid state may be deleted or reused at the agent's convence. If the entry is kept in the closed state, the values of the parameters associated with the entry must be correct. Closed implies the values in the circuit table are correct. The value of invalid indicates the other values in the table are invalid. Many agents may never return a value of invalid because they dynamically allocate and free unused table entries. An agent for a statically configured systems can return invalid to indicate the entry has not yet been used so the counters contain no information.

x25CircuitEstablishTime.name: x25CircuitEstablishTime
x25CircuitEstablishTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the channel was associated with this circuit. For outgoing SVCs, this is the time the first call packet was sent. For incoming SVCs, this is the time the call indication was received. For PVCs this is the time the PVC was able to pass data to a higher layer entity without loss of data.

x25CircuitDirection.name: x25CircuitDirection
x25CircuitDirection.description: The direction of the call that established this circuit.

x25CircuitInOctets.name: x25CircuitInOctets
x25CircuitInOctets.description: The number of octets of user data delivered to upper layer.

x25CircuitInPdus.name: x25CircuitInPdus
x25CircuitInPdus.description: The number of PDUs received for this circuit.

x25CircuitInRemotelyInitiatedResets.name: x25CircuitInRemotelyInitiatedResets
x25CircuitInRemotelyInitiatedResets.description: The number of Resets received for this circuit with cause code of DTE initiated.

x25CircuitInProviderInitiatedResets.name: x25CircuitInProviderInitiatedResets
x25CircuitInProviderInitiatedResets.description: The number of Resets received for this circuit with cause code other than DTE initiated.

x25CircuitInInterrupts.name: x25CircuitInInterrupts
x25CircuitInInterrupts.description: The number of interrupt packets received for this circuit.

x25CircuitOutOctets.name: x25CircuitOutOctets
x25CircuitOutOctets.description: The number of octets of user data sent for this circuit.

x25CircuitOutPdus.name: x25CircuitOutPdus
x25CircuitOutPdus.description: The number of PDUs sent for this circuit.

x25CircuitOutInterrupts.name: x25CircuitOutInterrupts
x25CircuitOutInterrupts.description: The number of interrupt packets sent on this circuit.

x25CircuitDataRetransmissionTimeouts.name: x25CircuitDataRetransmissionTimeouts
x25CircuitDataRetransmissionTimeouts.description: The number of times the T25 data retransmission timer expired for this circuit.

x25CircuitResetTimeouts.name: x25CircuitResetTimeouts
x25CircuitResetTimeouts.description: The number of times the T22 reset timer expired for this circuit.

x25CircuitInterruptTimeouts.name: x25CircuitInterruptTimeouts
x25CircuitInterruptTimeouts.description: The number of times the T26 Interrupt timer expired for this circuit.

x25CircuitCallParamId.name: x25CircuitCallParamId
x25CircuitCallParamId.description: This identifies the instance of the x25CallParmIndex for the entry in the x25CallParmTable which contains the call parameters in use with this circuit. The entry referenced must contain the values that are currently in use by the circuit rather than proposed values. A value of NULL indicates the circuit is a PVC or is using all the default parameters.

x25CircuitCalledDteAddress.name: x25CircuitCalledDteAddress
x25CircuitCalledDteAddress.description: For incoming calls, this is the called address from the call indication packet. For outgoing calls, this is the called address from the call confirmation packet. This will be zero length for PVCs.

x25CircuitCallingDteAddress.name: x25CircuitCallingDteAddress
x25CircuitCallingDteAddress.description: For incoming calls, this is the calling address from the call indication packet. For outgoing calls, this is the calling address from the call confirmation packet. This will be zero length for PVCs.

x25CircuitOriginallyCalledAddress.name: x25CircuitOriginallyCalledAddress
x25CircuitOriginallyCalledAddress.description: For incoming calls, this is the address in the call Redirection or Call Deflection Notification facility if the call was deflected or redirected, otherwise it will be called address from the call indication packet. For outgoing calls, this is the address from the call request packet. This will be zero length for PVCs.

x25CircuitDescr.name: x25CircuitDescr
x25CircuitDescr.description: A descriptive string associated with this circuit. This provides a place for the agent to supply any descriptive information it knows about the use or owner of the circuit. The agent may return the process identifier and user name for the process using the circuit. Alternative the agent may return the name of the configuration entry that caused a bridge to establish the circuit. A zero length value indicates the agent doesn't have any additional information.

x25CallParmTable.name: x25CallParmTable
x25CallParmTable.description: These objects contain the parameters that can be varied between X.25 calls. The entries in this table are independent of the PLE. There exists only one of these tables for the entire system. The indexes for the entries are independent of any PLE or any circuit. Other tables reference entries in this table. Entries in this table can be used for default PLE parameters, for parameters to use to place/answer a call, for the parameters currently in use for a circuit, or parameters that were used by a circuit. The number of references to a given set of parameters can be found in the x25CallParmRefCount object sharing the same instance identifier with the parameters. The value of this reference count also affects the access of the objects in this table. An object in this table with the same instance identifier as the instance identifier of an x25CallParmRefCount must be consider associated with that reference count. An object with an associated reference count of zero can be written (if its ACCESS clause allows it). An object with an associated reference count greater than zero can not be written (regardless of the ACCESS clause). This ensures that a set of call parameters being referenced from another table can not be modified or changed in a ways inappropriate for continued use by that table.

x25CallParmIndex.name: x25CallParmIndex
x25CallParmIndex.description: A value that distinguishes this entry from another entry. Entries in this table are referenced from other objects which identify call parameters. It is impossible to know which other objects in the MIB reference entries in the table by looking at this table. Because of this, changes to parameters must be accomplished by creating a new entry in this table and then changing the referencing table to identify the new entry. Note that an agent will only use the values in this table when another table is changed to reference those values. The number of other tables that reference an index object in this table can be found in x25CallParmRefCount. The value of the reference count will affect the writability of the objects as explained above. Entries in this table which have a reference count of zero maybe deleted at the convence of the agent. Care should be taken by the agent to give the NMS sufficient time to create a reference to newly created entries. Should a Management Station not find a free index with which to create a new entry, it may feel free to delete entries with a reference count of zero. However in doing so the Management Station much realize it may impact other Management Stations.

x25CallParmStatus.name: x25CallParmStatus
x25CallParmStatus.description: The status of this call parameter entry. See RFC 1271 for details of usage.

x25CallParmRefCount.name: x25CallParmRefCount
x25CallParmRefCount.description: The number of references know by a management station to exist to this set of call parameters. This is the number of other objects that have returned a value of, and will return a value of, the index for this set of call parameters. Examples of such objects are the x25AdmnDefCallParamId, x25OperDataLinkId, or x25AdmnDefCallParamId objects defined above.

x25CallParmInPacketSize.name: x25CallParmInPacketSize
x25CallParmInPacketSize.description: The maximum receive packet size in octets for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE means use a default size of 128.

x25CallParmOutPacketSize.name: x25CallParmOutPacketSize
x25CallParmOutPacketSize.description: The maximum transmit packet size in octets for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE default means use a default size of 128.

x25CallParmInWindowSize.name: x25CallParmInWindowSize
x25CallParmInWindowSize.description: The receive window size for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE default means use 2.

x25CallParmOutWindowSize.name: x25CallParmOutWindowSize
x25CallParmOutWindowSize.description: The transmit window size for a circuit. A size of zero for a circuit means use the PLE default size. A size of zero for the PLE default means use 2.

x25CallParmAcceptReverseCharging.name: x25CallParmAcceptReverseCharging
x25CallParmAcceptReverseCharging.description: An enumeration defining if the PLE will accept or refuse charges. A value of default for a circuit means use the PLE default value. A value of neverAccept is only used for the PLE default and indicates the PLE will never accept reverse charging. A value of default for a PLE default means refuse.

x25CallParmProposeReverseCharging.name: x25CallParmProposeReverseCharging
x25CallParmProposeReverseCharging.description: An enumeration defining if the PLE should propose reverse or local charging. The value of default for a circuit means use the PLE default. The value of default for the PLE default means use local.

x25CallParmFastSelect.name: x25CallParmFastSelect
x25CallParmFastSelect.description: Expresses preference for use of fast select facility. The value of default for a circuit is the PLE default. A value of default for the PLE means noFastSelect. A value of noFastSelect or noRestrictedFastResponse indicates a circuit may not use fast select or restricted fast response.

x25CallParmInThruPutClasSize.name: x25CallParmInThruPutClasSize
x25CallParmInThruPutClasSize.description: The incoming throughput class to negotiate. A value of tcDefault for a circuit means use the PLE default. A value of tcDefault for the PLE default means tcNone. A value of tcNone means do not negotiate throughtput class.

x25CallParmOutThruPutClasSize.name: x25CallParmOutThruPutClasSize
x25CallParmOutThruPutClasSize.description: The outgoing throughput class to negotiate. A value of tcDefault for a circuit means use the PLE default. A value of tcDefault for the PLE default means use tcNone. A value of tcNone means do not negotiate throughtput class.

x25CallParmCug.name: x25CallParmCug
x25CallParmCug.description: The Closed User Group to specify. This consists of two or four octets containing the characters 0 through 9. A zero length string indicates no facility requested. A string length of three containing the characters DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default, (the PLE default parameter may not reference an entry of DEF.)

x25CallParmCugoa.name: x25CallParmCugoa
x25CallParmCugoa.description: The Closed User Group with Outgoing Access to specify. This consists of two or four octets containing the characters 0 through 9. A string length of three containing the characters DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default (the PLE default parameters may not reference an entry of DEF). A zero length string indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmBcug.name: x25CallParmBcug
x25CallParmBcug.description: The Bilateral Closed User Group to specify. This consists of two octets containing the characters 0 through 9. A string length of three containing the characters DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default (the PLE default parameter may not reference an entry of DEF). A zero length string indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmNui.name: x25CallParmNui
x25CallParmNui.description: The Network User Identifier facility. This is binary value to be included immediately after the length field. The PLE will supply the length octet. A zero length string indicates no facility requested. This value is ignored for the PLE default parameters entry.

x25CallParmChargingInfo.name: x25CallParmChargingInfo
x25CallParmChargingInfo.description: The charging Information facility. A value of default for a circuit means use the PLE default. The value of default for the default PLE parameters means use noFacility. The value of noFacility means do not include a facility.

x25CallParmRpoa.name: x25CallParmRpoa
x25CallParmRpoa.description: The RPOA facility. The octet string contains n * 4 sequences of the characters 0-9 to specify a facility with n entries. The octet string containing the 3 characters DEF for a circuit specifies use of the PLE default (the entry for the PLE default may not contain DEF). A zero length string indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmTrnstDly.name: x25CallParmTrnstDly
x25CallParmTrnstDly.description: The Transit Delay Selection and Indication value. A value of 65536 indicates no facility requested. A value of 65537 for a circuit means use the PLE default (the PLE default parameters entry may not use the value 65537). The value 65535 may only be used to indicate the value in use by a circuit.

x25CallParmCallingExt.name: x25CallParmCallingExt
x25CallParmCallingExt.description: The Calling Extension facility. This contains one of the following: A sequence of hex digits with the value to be put in the facility. These digits will be converted to binary by the agent and put in the facility. These octets do not include the length octet. A value containing the three character DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default, (the entry for the PLE default parameters may not use the value DEF). A zero length string indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmCalledExt.name: x25CallParmCalledExt
x25CallParmCalledExt.description: The Called Extension facility. This contains one of the following: A sequence of hex digits with the value to be put in the facility. These digits will be converted to binary by the agent and put in the facility. These octets do not include the length octet. A value containing the three character DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default, (the entry for the PLE default parameters may not use the value DEF). A zero length string indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmInMinThuPutCls.name: x25CallParmInMinThuPutCls
x25CallParmInMinThuPutCls.description: The minimum input throughput Class. A value of 16 for a circuit means use the PLE default (the PLE parameters entry may not use this value). A value of 17 indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmOutMinThuPutCls.name: x25CallParmOutMinThuPutCls
x25CallParmOutMinThuPutCls.description: The minimum output throughput Class. A value of 16 for a circuit means use the PLE default (the PLE parameters entry may not use this value). A value of 17 indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmEndTrnsDly.name: x25CallParmEndTrnsDly
x25CallParmEndTrnsDly.description: The End-to-End Transit Delay to negotiate. An octet string of length 2, 4, or 6 contains the facility encoded as specified in ISO/IEC 8208 section 15.3.2.4. An octet string of length 3 containing the three character DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default (the entry for the PLE default can not contain the characters DEF). A zero length string indicates no facility requested.

x25CallParmPriority.name: x25CallParmPriority
x25CallParmPriority.description: The priority facility to negotiate. The octet string encoded as specified in ISO/IEC 8208 section 15.3.2.5. A zero length string indicates no facility requested. The entry for the PLE default parameters must be zero length.

x25CallParmProtection.name: x25CallParmProtection
x25CallParmProtection.description: A string contains the following: A hex string containing the value for the protection facility. This will be converted from hex to the octets actually in the packet by the agent. The agent will supply the length field and the length octet is not contained in this string. An string containing the 3 characters DEF for a circuit means use the PLE default (the entry for the PLE default parameters may not use the value DEF). A zero length string mean no facility requested.

x25CallParmExptData.name: x25CallParmExptData
x25CallParmExptData.description: The Expedited Data facility to negotiate. A value of default for a circuit means use the PLE default value. The entry for the PLE default parameters may not have the value default.

x25CallParmUserData.name: x25CallParmUserData
x25CallParmUserData.description: The call user data as placed in the packet. A zero length string indicates no call user data. If both the circuit call parameters and the PLE default have call user data defined, the data from the circuit call parameters will be used. If only the PLE has data defined, the PLE entry will be used. If neither the circuit call parameters or the PLE default entry has a value, no call user data will be sent.

x25CallParmCallingNetworkFacilities.name: x25CallParmCallingNetworkFacilities
x25CallParmCallingNetworkFacilities.description: The calling network facilities. The facilities are encoded here exactly as encoded in the call packet. These facilities do not include the marker facility code. A zero length string in the entry for the parameter to use when establishing a circuit means use the PLE default. A zero length string in the entry for PLE default parameters indicates no default facilities.

x25CallParmCalledNetworkFacilities.name: x25CallParmCalledNetworkFacilities
x25CallParmCalledNetworkFacilities.description: The called network facilities. The facilities are encoded here exactly as encoded in the call packet. These facilities do not include the marker facility code. A zero length string in the entry for the parameter to use when establishing a circuit means use the PLE default. A zero length string in the entry for PLE default parameters indicates no default facilities.

x25Restart.name: x25Restart
x25Restart.description: This trap means the X.25 PLE sent or received a restart packet. The restart that brings up the link should not send a x25Restart trap so the interface should send a linkUp trap. Sending this trap means the agent does not send a linkDown and linkUp trap.

x25Reset.name: x25Reset
x25Reset.description: If the PLE sends or receives a reset, the agent should send an x25Reset trap.
